&lt;h1 id="the-future-of-startup-funding"&gt;The Future of Startup Funding&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Want to start a startup? Get funded by Y Combinator.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;August 2010&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Two years ago I wrote about what I called &amp;ldquo;a huge, unexploited opportunity in startup funding:&amp;rdquo; the growing disconnect between VCs, whose current business model requires them to invest large amounts, and a large class of startups that need less than they used to. Increasingly, startups want a couple hundred thousand dollars, not a couple million. [1]&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>